  <p>
    Since opening in Pondok Indah in September 2021, The Independent School of Jakarta has been covered by education media, national and international press, and specialist publications. The articles below represent a selection of that coverage, grouped by topic.
  </p>

  <!-- ─── Rankings & Recognition ─── -->
  <h2>Rankings and Recognition</h2>

  <p>
    In early 2026, ISJ was ranked the number one international school in Jakarta on the world's leading international schools platform, with the ranking covered across education and legal publications in the UK and United States.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.international-schools-database.com/in/jakarta/the-independent-school-of-jakarta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">International Schools Database — ISJ School Profile and Rankings</a></li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    ISJ is also featured in the Grokipedia encyclopaedia and the Bahasa Indonesia Wikipedia, reflecting the school's established presence in both the global education community and the local Indonesian context.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://grokipedia.com/page/The_Independent_School_of_Jakarta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Grokipedia — The Independent School of Jakarta</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Independent_School_of_Jakarta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wikipedia (Bahasa Indonesia) — The Independent School of Jakarta</a></li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ─── The Schools Trust ─── -->
  <h2>The Schools Trust Partnership</h2>

  <p>
    ISJ's alignment with The Schools Trust was covered by international newswires in October 2025. The partnership provides ISJ with governance and educational oversight from a UK-registered charity with a track record of excellent inspection results across its school network.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.einpresswire.com/article/861511931/british-international-school-joins-the-schools-trust-aligns-with-uk-group-delivering-excellent-inspection-results" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EIN Presswire — British International School Joins The Schools Trust (October 2025)</a></li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ─── UK Boarding Pathways ─── -->
  <h2>British Boarding School Pathways</h2>

  <p>
    In January 2026, ISJ announced a partnership with Ipswich High School to create direct pathways into British boarding education for its first cohort of senior pupils. The announcement was carried by EIN Presswire and picked up by international education media.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.einpresswire.com/article/884702537/isj-creates-british-boarding-school-pathways-for-its-first-cohort-of-senior-pupils" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EIN Presswire — ISJ Creates British Boarding School Pathways (January 2026)</a></li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ─── TES Awards ─── -->
  <h2>TES Awards for International Schools</h2>

  <p>
    ISJ teaching assistant Intan Dewiyani was shortlisted for the Teaching Assistant of the Year category at the TES Awards for International Schools 2025, one of the most widely recognised accolades in international education. The shortlist was covered by School Management Plus and the TES itself.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.schoolmanagementplus.com/heads-governors-school-leadership-governance/shortlist-published-for-tes-awards-for-international-schools/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">School Management Plus — TES Awards for International Schools 2025 Shortlist</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.tes.com/schools-awards/international/shortlist" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TES — Awards for International Schools: Full Shortlist</a></li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ─── Ki Hajar Dewantara Scholarship ─── -->
  <h2>Ki Hajar Dewantara Scholarship</h2>

  <p>
    ISJ's flagship scholarship programme for high-achieving Indonesian students has been covered across the Indonesian press since its launch. Coverage has included <em>Observer ID</em>, <em>What's New Indonesia</em>, and a number of Indonesian-language education publications.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://observerid.com/isj-unique-opportunity-for-indonesian-pupils-to-study-at-leading-british-international-school/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Observer ID — Unique Opportunity for Indonesian Pupils to Study at ISJ</a></li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ─── Founding Head Profile ─── -->
  <h2>School Profile and Leadership</h2>

  <p>
    In May 2021, ahead of ISJ's opening, Indonesia Expat published a profile of founding Head Emma Webb, covering her background in British independent education and the vision for the new school.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://indonesiaexpat.id/business-property/business-profile/nurture-pupils-into-independent-and-skilled-individuals-with-emma-webb/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Indonesia Expat — Nurture Pupils into Independent and Skilled Individuals with Emma Webb (May 2021)</a></li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    ISJ is also listed among the top international schools in Jakarta in the annual <em>Little Steps Asia</em> school guide, a widely read resource for expat families across Southeast Asia.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.littlestepsasia.com/jakarta/learn/schools/top-international-schools-in-jakarta-indonesia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Little Steps Asia — Top International Schools in Jakarta 2026</a></li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Families researching ISJ alongside other South Jakarta options can compare schools, fees, and commute times using ISJ's own <a href="/insights/best-international-schools-jakarta">guide to international schools in Jakarta</a>.
  </p>

